"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:4.3.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">4.3.1</span> Tabernacle: Washstand, basin, bowl</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">כִּיּוֹר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kiyor)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:18\">EXO 30:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:28\">EXO 30:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:9\">EXO 31:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:16\">EXO 35:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:8\">EXO 38:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:39\">EXO 39:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:7\">EXO 40:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:11\">EXO 40:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:30\">EXO 40:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:11\">LEV 8:11</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The basin was a large copper pot that stood on a copper base. It was used by the priests to wash their hands and feet. It was probably open at the top for filling with water and may have had spouts near the bottom to allow the water to run out. According to <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:18\">EXO 30:18</a>, it stood “between the tent of meeting and the altar” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr>).</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The priests were commanded to wash their hands and feet before beginning their daily work. This was a ceremonial act of purification for which the basin held the water.</p>\n<p>The word “laver,” used by some English translations (for example, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> and <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Jewish Publication Society Version\">NJPSV</abbr>), is obscure and communicates little to the average reader. <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> “bowl” is likely to be perceived as something much smaller than its actual size. It is better to say “large bowl” (so <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr>) or “large basin.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
